(
<emphasis box="[643,783,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Pseudofusus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[799,914,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">pulchellus</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,333,1043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,441,468]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Material examined:</emphasis>
five 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[497,586,442,467]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[497,586,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shells labelled by Monterosato “ 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bellini-Capri" authorityName="Bellini-Capri" box="[963,1352,441,468]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Dentifusus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[963,1162,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Dentifusus curtus</emphasis>
, Bellini—Capri
</taxonomicName>
!” (MC- CIC—drawer 8, n. 146) actually belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Buzzurro &amp; Russo, 2007" authorityName="Buzzurro &amp; Russo" authorityYear="2007" box="[626,1116,477,504]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[626,835,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusinus alternatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Buzzurro, G. &amp; Russo, P." box="[841,1116,477,504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" refId="ref16038" refString="Buzzurro, G. &amp; Russo, P. (2007) Fusinus del Mediterraneo. Privately published, 280 pp." type="book" year="2007">Buzzurro &amp; Russo, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(4 shells) and presumably to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Philippi, 1840)" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[151,542,513,539]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis box="[151,360,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusinus pulchellus</emphasis>
(Philippi, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
(1 shell) (
<figureCitation box="[653,742,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1460,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,395,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,414,1432]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Bittium iadertinum var. coralligena. A. Original figures. B. Possible type material from Capri Island (Naples)—4.9×1.5 mm. C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCZR—not numbered. D, E. Murex trunculus var. propeconglobata. D. Fossil(?) shell from Sciacca (Agrigento)—72.4×52.8 mm. E. Original label handwritten by Monterosato. MCZR- M-7623. F, G. Fusus (Pseudofusus) pulchellus var. curta. F. Original figures. G. Shells from Capri Island (Naples) and original label handwritten by Monterosato (up to 16 mm in total height). MCCIC—drawer 8, n. 146. H. Clathromangilia granum var. prausi. Original figures. I. Left. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. minimum. Original figure. I. Right. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. paludosum. Original figures." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449572/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
); seventeen shells labelled by Monterosato “ 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bellini-Capri" authorityName="Bellini-Capri" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Dentifusus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[1234,1429,514,540]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Dentifusus curtus</emphasis>
, Bellini—Capri
</taxonomicName>
!! Dr. Cerio—1904” (MCZR-M-17457) again mostly belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buzzurro &amp; Russo" authorityYear="2007" box="[1047,1191,549,575]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1191,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">F. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This material comes from the same 
<typeStatus box="[318,366,586,612]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1902 a" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1902" box="[495,1133,585,612]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="pulchellus" subGenus="Pseudofusus" variety="curta">
<emphasis box="[495,562,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[578,718,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Pseudofusus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[734,849,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">pulchellus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[905,964,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">curta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[971,1133,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini, 1902a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="354" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,333,1043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,622,648]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted on the basis of insignificant morphological characteristics, we rank it infrasubspecific, and thus not available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[549,683,657,683]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 
<date box="[743,838,657,684]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" value="1945-10-02">10.2, 45</date>
.5, 45.6, glossary). This taxon was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Snyder, M. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="354" pagination="1 - 431" refId="ref19317" refString="Snyder, M. A. (2003) Catalogue of the marine gastropod family Fasciolariidae. Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 21, 1 - 431." type="journal article" year="2003">Snyder (2003)</bibRefCitation>
as described in 1929, whereas by 
<bibRefCitation author="Russo, P." box="[613,763,693,720]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" pagination="160 - 179" refId="ref18949" refString="Russo, P. (2018) Recent Mediterranean Fusinus (Gastropoda: Fasciolariidae) in the Monterosato collection of the Museo Civico di Zoologia of Rome. Bollettino Malacologico, 54, 160 - 179." type="journal article" year="2018">Russo (2018)</bibRefCitation>
as in 1901, but its publication date is here stated in 1902. It would be also preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Fleming, 1828" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1828" box="[496,813,729,755]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[496,641,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusus curtus</emphasis>
Fleming, 1828
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeffreys, 1867" authorityName="Jeffreys" authorityYear="1867" box="[869,1183,729,755]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[869,1014,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusus curtus</emphasis>
Jeffreys, 1867
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Russo, P." box="[1195,1346,729,756]" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" pagination="160 - 179" refId="ref18949" refString="Russo, P. (2018) Recent Mediterranean Fusinus (Gastropoda: Fasciolariidae) in the Monterosato collection of the Museo Civico di Zoologia of Rome. Bollettino Malacologico, 54, 160 - 179." type="journal article" year="2018">Russo (2018)</bibRefCitation>
considered it as described on the basis of a juvenile 
<taxonomicName box="[658,800,765,791]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis box="[658,800,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">F. pulchellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, missing a part of the siphonal canal. We cannot confirm here the above-mentioned misidentification as the figure attached to its description is very poor. Noteworthy, 
<bibRefCitation author="Russo, P." pageId="11" pageNumber="354" pagination="160 - 179" refId="ref18949" refString="Russo, P. (2018) Recent Mediterranean Fusinus (Gastropoda: Fasciolariidae) in the Monterosato collection of the Museo Civico di Zoologia of Rome. Bollettino Malacologico, 54, 160 - 179." type="journal article" year="2018">Russo (2018)</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned that a specimen from Capri Island stored in Monterosato’s collection (Rome, 
<collectingCountry box="[1290,1343,837,864]" name="Italy" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Italy</collectingCountry>
) and labelled as “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini" authorityName="Bellini" box="[272,578,873,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Pseudofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[272,491,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Pseudofusus curtus</emphasis>
Bellini
</taxonomicName>
” actually belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buzzurro &amp; Russo" authorityYear="2007" box="[819,962,873,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[819,962,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">F. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also faced a similar issue (see above in additional material), which may suggest that at least Monterosato conceived 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1902" box="[1047,1436,909,936]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="pulchellus" variety="curta">
<emphasis box="[1047,1236,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusus pulchellus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1293,1352,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">curta</emphasis>
Bellini
</taxonomicName>
as belonging to what is now identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buzzurro &amp; Russo" authorityYear="2007" box="[628,771,945,971]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis box="[628,771,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">F. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, the usage of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafinesque, 1815" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1142,1436,945,972]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1142,1231,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusinus</emphasis>
Rafinesque, 1815
</taxonomicName>
should be actually restricted to a group of Indo-West Pacific species related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758) (Vermeij &amp; Snyder 2018)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="354" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1176,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="354">Fusinus colus</emphasis>
(
